org.rsna.ctp.objects

Class FileObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.objects.FileObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DicomObject, XmlObject, ZipObject

    public class FileObject
extends java.lang.Object
    A generic file object providing methods for moving, renaming, and copying a file. This is the base class for MIRC data files used for DICOM images and clinical trial metadata (both XML and zip).

      • setExtension

        public java.io.File setExtension(java.lang.String extension)
        Set the file's extension (the last period and the characters after it in the file name). If the current extension is ".md", it is replaced the supplied extension. If the current extension is already equal to the supplied extension, the file is not renamed. If the current extension is anything else, the supplied extension is appended to the filename.
        Returns:
        the file after any modification.

      • renameTo

        public boolean renameTo(java.io.File newFile)
        Rename the file. If the supplied pathname is a directory, the file is renamed into the directory and given the same filename it had before. If the supplied pathname is not a directory, the file is renamed to the supplied pathname. This method also changes the File returned by getFile() so that it points to the renamed data file. Use this method to move the file within the same file system.
        Parameters:
        newFile - the new pathname of the file, or the pathname of the directory into which to rename the file.
        Returns:
        true if the rename was successful, false otherwise.

      • renameToUID

        public boolean renameToUID()
        Rename the file to its UID, setting the standard extension.
        Returns:
        true if the rename was successful, false otherwise.

      • copyTo

        public boolean copyTo(java.io.File destination)
        Copy the object's file. The original file is not deleted.
        Parameters:
        destination - the File pointing to where the copy is to be written.
        Returns:
        true if the operation succeeded completely; false otherwise.

      • copyToDirectory

        public java.io.File copyToDirectory(java.io.File dir)
        Copy the object's file to a directory, assigning a new name if necessary. The original file is not deleted and the FileObject is unmodified.
        Parameters:
        dir - the File pointing to the directory into which the copy is to be written.
        Returns:
        the File pointing to the copy if the operation succeeded completely; null otherwise.

      • moveTo

        public boolean moveTo(java.io.File newFile)
        Move the object's data file, and remove it from its previous location. If the supplied pathname is a directory, the file is moved into the directory and given the same filename it had before. If the supplied pathname is not a directory, the file is given the name defined by the pathname. This method will overwrite a file with the same name in the destination directory. This method attempts to do the move with a rename, and only copies the file if the rename fails. This method also changes the File returned by getFile() so that it points to the data file in its new location. Use this method to move the file between file systems.
        Parameters:
        newFile - the new name of the file.
        Returns:
        true if the move was successful, false otherwise.

      • moveToDirectory

        public boolean moveToDirectory(java.io.File dir,
                      boolean overwrite)
        Move the object's data file into a directory and remove it from its previous location. This method changes the File returned by getFile() so that it points to the data file in its new location. This method creates the directory if it does not already exist.
        Parameters:
        dir - the directory into which to move the data file.
        overwrite - true if the file is to be allowed to overwrite an existing file with the same name in the destination directory; false if a new name is to be created to prevent overwriting a file.
        Returns:
        true if the move was successful, false otherwise.

      • moveToDirectory

        public boolean moveToDirectory(java.io.File dir)
        Move the object's data file into a directory, creating a new name for the file if the filename already exists in the directory, and remove the file from its previous location. This method will therefore not overwrite an existing file. This method also changes the File returned by getFile() so that it points to the data file in its new location. This method creates the directory if it does not already exist. This method is intended for placing FileObjects into a holding directory.
        Parameters:
        dir - the directory into which to move the data file.
        Returns:
        true if the move was successful, false otherwise.

      • moveToDirectory

        public boolean moveToDirectory(java.io.File dir,
                      java.lang.String name)
        Move the object's data file into a directory, using the specified filename. If the filename already exists in the directory, create a new name for the file. Remove the file from its previous location. This method therefore does not overwrite an existing file. This method also changes the File returned by getFile() so that it points to the data file in its new location. This method creates the directory if it does not already exist. This method is intended for placing FileObjects into a document's directory.
        Parameters:
        dir - the directory into which to move the data file.
        name - the name to use for the file in the new directory.
        Returns:
        true if the move was successful, false otherwise.

      • hasMatchingExtension

        public boolean hasMatchingExtension(java.lang.String[] textext,
                           boolean excludeSubclasses)
        Determine whether this FileObject has an extension matching one of the entries in an array. The method can exclude FileObject subclasses (DicomObject, ZipObject, and XmlObject).
        Parameters:
        textext - the array of extensions. Each entry must start with a period (e.g., ".txt").
        excludeSubclasses - true if subclasses are to be rejected; false if all FileObjects are to be tested.
        Returns:
        true if this FileObject has a matching extension; false otherwise.
